    "created_at": "2013-04-16T15:35:13Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-04-16T15:35:13Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "As you discovered the IPython kernel runs independently of the IPython console, and details such as terminal encodings aren't passed from the IPython console to the kernel.  One big issue here is that multiple consoles (each with different preferred encodings) can connect to the same kernel.  If I remember correctly, UTF-8 was chosen because of it's commonality and ability to represent the entire unicode spectrum.\n\nPerhaps we should make an IPython configurable for the kernel stdout encoding?\n\nAre there any other ideas for how to tackle this problem?\n"
  },
