    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "How about supporting multiple `_repr_*` at sympy side?  This is what sympy extension already does, right?  This solution fits well with multiple console architecture of IPython.  I think there are several ways to implement this: (1) add `__repr_pprint_unicode_` and restrict `__repr_pprint_` to use only ascii characters; (2) define `_repr_pprint_` using ascii and also define `_repr_json_` to send equation as AST; then sympy can register extension to convert `_repr_json_` to unicode at client side, if the client support unicode output.\n\nAdditionally, I think terminal client should convert unicode into the encoding supported by the terminal (with 'replace' or something).\n"
  },
