    "updated_at": "2013-04-16T16:52:45Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think it's up to the terminal client to take care of that - the kernel doesn't and shouldn't know what the frontend can display, and we're not about to start limiting ourselves to ascii. The Notebook, the Qt console and modern Linux & Mac terminals are all Unicode capable.\n\n@tkf - this isn't just about the displayhook framework, though - sympy.pprint is actually calling `print`, which writes to stdout without touching our display machinery.\n"
  },
