    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@takluyver  I was suggest to _not_ using pprint.  I guess it is very hard to make pprint useful if IPython client converts it to non-unicode string at client side.  How can IPython client construct meaningful equation from a unicode string when it can't use unicode?\n\nBut I agree that client should do something when unicode is sent via stdout/err, to avoid encoding error.  That was the last point in the above comment.\n"
  },
