    "updated_at": "2013-04-24T21:47:44Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "For SymPy's use case it would be important to know what the client supports so that the printing is setup accordingly. If we are in a console client we need to know which encoding it is using and we don't need to generate LaTeX; if we are in a notebook we would generate the LaTeX; and if we are in the qtconsole or a notebook with --no-mathjax then we additionally need LaTeX-rendered pngs.\n"
  },
